# Cursor Rules for Trip AI Planner

You are an expert developer working on Trip AI Planner — an AI-powered travel planning app for Asia-Pacific destinations.
Follow these rules precisely when generating or modifying code.

## Tech Stack

| Layer      | Technology                                                          |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Framework  | Next.js 15 (App Router, standalone output)                          |
| Language   | TypeScript (ES2022, bundler resolution, `@/*` path alias)           |
| UI         | React 19, Tailwind CSS 3, Framer Motion                             |
| Components | Radix UI (Dialog, Popover, Slot), Lucide React icons, Vaul (drawer) |
| State      | Zustand 5 (with `persist` middleware for auth)                      |
| AI         | Google Gemini (`@google/genai`, model: `gemini-3-flash-preview`)    |
| Auth       | Firebase Auth (email/password + Google OAuth)                       |
| Maps       | Leaflet 1.9 (dynamic import, SSR-disabled)                          |
| i18n       | Custom `translations` object in `src/utils/i18n.ts`                 |
| Weather    | Visual Crossing API                                                 |
| Styling    | `cn()` helper from `@/lib/utils` using `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`    |
| Testing    | Playwright                                                          |
| Formatting | Prettier                                                            |
| Deployment | Vercel (also Docker + Nginx available)                              |

## Core Principles

- **YAGNI** — Only build what's needed now
- **KISS** — Simple, readable solutions over clever abstractions
- **DRY** — Shared logic in hooks/utils/services
- **SOLID** — Single responsibility per file; depend on abstractions
- **Mobile-first** — Design for mobile, enhance for desktop
- **Server-safe keys** — Never expose API keys to the browser

## Project Structure

```
app/                    # Next.js App Router
  layout.tsx            # Root layout (Inter font, MobileGestureProvider)
  page.tsx              # Entry — renders <App />
  globals.css           # Tailwind directives, Leaflet CSS
  api/ai/route.ts       # AI proxy (protects Gemini API key)
  api/weather/route.ts  # Weather proxy
src/
  App.tsx               # Main client component (feature routing, auth guard)
  types.ts              # Shared type definitions
  components/
    features/           # auth/, trip-planner/, weather/
    layout/             # AppShell, Header, Sidebar, BottomNav
    providers/          # MobileGestureProvider
    ui/                 # DatePicker (reusable primitives)
    Icons.tsx           # CategoryIcon, getCategoryColor
    Map.tsx             # Leaflet map wrapper
  hooks/                # useMediaQuery, useIsMobile, useIsDesktop
  lib/
    firebase.ts         # Client-side Firebase init
    firebase-admin.ts   # Server-side Firebase Admin
    utils.ts            # cn() helper
  services/
    aiClient.ts         # Browser → /api/ai fetch wrapper
    geminiService.ts    # Server-side Gemini calls (structured output)
    promptService.ts    # All AI prompt templates
    placesService.ts    # Place autocomplete (local JSON)
    geolocationService.ts
    weatherService.ts
  stores/               # Zustand stores (appStore, tripStore, authStore, weatherStore)
  utils/
    currency.ts         # VND/USD formatting
    i18n.ts             # translations object (vi, en)
```

## File Naming

- **Components:** PascalCase (`SearchPanel.tsx`)
- **Hooks:** camelCase with `use` prefix (`useMediaQuery.ts`)
- **Stores:** camelCase with `Store` suffix (`tripStore.ts`)
- **Services:** camelCase with `Service` suffix (`geminiService.ts`)
- **Utils:** camelCase (`currency.ts`)
- **Barrel exports:** `index.ts` in feature folders

## UI Primitives — Always Use These

| Component       | Import                       | Use Instead Of          |
| --------------- | ---------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| `DatePicker`    | `@/components/ui/DatePicker` | `<input type="date">`   |
| `CategoryIcon`  | `@/components/Icons`         | Inline icon switches    |
| `cn()`          | `@/lib/utils`                | Manual className concat |
| Radix `Dialog`  | `@radix-ui/react-dialog`     | Custom modals           |
| Radix `Popover` | `@radix-ui/react-popover`    | Custom dropdowns        |
| `Vaul` Drawer   | `vaul`                       | Custom bottom sheets    |
| Lucide icons    | `lucide-react`               | Raw SVGs                |

## State Management

- Zustand for all global state — one store per domain
- Access via hooks: `useAppStore()`, `useTripStore()`, `useAuthStore()`
- `persist` middleware only for page-reload survival (e.g., `authStore`)
- Keep stores flat; derive computed values in components
- Never import stores in server components

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS only — no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Use `cn()` for conditional classes
- Mobile breakpoint: `md:` (768px), design mobile-first
- Font: Inter via `next/font/google`
- Colors: Slate neutrals, Blue/Indigo primary, contextual category colors

## API / Backend Pattern

- Browser calls `aiClient.ts` → `POST /api/ai` → `geminiService.ts`
- Never import `geminiService.ts` or access server env vars on the client
- All AI responses use Gemini structured output (`responseSchema`)
- Prompts centralized in `promptService.ts`
- Auth: Firebase ID token as `Bearer` in `Authorization` header
- Guest users: 3 free prompts, then auth wall

## i18n

- Translations in `src/utils/i18n.ts` — `vi` and `en` keys
- Access: `const t = translations[language]` from `useAppStore()`
- Default language: Vietnamese (`vi`)
- All user-visible strings must use translations — never hardcode

## TypeScript

- Interfaces for object shapes, enums for fixed sets (`TravelMode`, `StopType`)
- Types in `src/types.ts`; feature-specific in `src/types/`
- Always use `@/*` path alias for `src/` imports
- Mark client components with `'use client'`
- Use `dynamic()` with `{ ssr: false }` for browser-only libs

## React Patterns

- Functional components with `React.FC<Props>`
- Destructure props in function signature
- SSR-safe: guard `window`/`navigator` with `typeof window !== 'undefined'`
- Custom hooks in `src/hooks/`

## Security

- Server-only: `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `VISUAL_CROSSING_API_KEY`, `FIREBASE_ADMIN_*`
- Client-safe: `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_*` vars
- Verify Firebase ID tokens in API routes via `firebase-admin`
- Sanitize user input before AI prompts

## Performance

- Dynamic import Leaflet with `ssr: false`
- `next/font` for font optimization
- Standalone output for minimal Docker images
- Lazy-load heavy features
- `useCallback`/`useMemo` only when profiling shows need

## Common Patterns

- Feature routing via `useAppStore().activeFeature` in `App.tsx`
- Mobile/desktop: `useIsMobile()` → conditional Header, BottomNav, Sidebar
- Place autocomplete: local JSON via `placesService.ts`
- Currency: store in VND, convert at display via `formatCurrency()`
- AI structured output: Gemini `responseSchema` for typed responses
- Cost estimation: select items → `CostSummary` computes totals

## What NOT to Do

- ❌ Import `geminiService.ts` or `firebase-admin.ts` in client components
- ❌ Use `process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY` on the client
- ❌ Hardcode UI strings — use `translations[language]`
- ❌ Use raw HTML elements when a UI primitive exists
- ❌ Create CSS files — use Tailwind classes
- ❌ Add derived state to Zustand stores
- ❌ Skip `'use client'` directive when using hooks/browser APIs
- ❌ Inline AI prompts — put all prompts in `promptService.ts`
- ❌ Store amounts in USD — always VND internally, convert at display
- ❌ Use `useEffect` for data fetching — prefer service layer

## Environment Variables

**Server-only:** `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `VISUAL_CROSSING_API_KEY`, `FIREBASE_ADMIN_*`
**Client-safe:** `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID`

## Run Commands

| Action          | Command                   |
| --------------- | ------------------------- |
| Dev server      | `npm run dev` (port 4200) |
| Build           | `npm run build`           |
| Start prod      | `npm start` (port 4200)   |
| Format          | `npm run format`          |
| Format check    | `npm run format:check`    |
| Generate places | `npm run generate:places` |
| E2E tests       | `npx playwright test`     |
